{
  "stem": "7458.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He too was being hidden by a farmer, who-- and Maishe actually spoke a very good Polish and looked like a Polish young man.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the farmer passed him off as a Pole and he survived as a member of that family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So when we came back to town, to Jasionowka, after the Russian army marched in, to amazement and surprise, I found that I had two sisters, one brother, and one niece who survived out of the whole family, plus my cousins, Schleime and Elichaim and Maishe and some friends.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was really a non-event event, because we were in the forest at the time and didn't even know that the Germans were no longer there and the Russians were now in control of that area.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We might have been there maybe for a day or two beyond liberation, not even realizing that we were already liberated.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But eventually, of course, I think we came back to Dekar's house, and we found out, yes, you are free people now.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You can go.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we went back to town.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] there were about-- Jasionowka was extremely lucky.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Many towns had no survivors at all, some of them, one or two.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Elie Wiesel, I believe only one or two other people survived from his hometown.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Many towns had not a single person survive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Jasionowka, actually about 125 people survived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the reason was that Jasionowka was one of the last towns to be liquidated.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All the other towns were liquidated months and weeks before Jasionowka.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Only Bialystok and Jasionowka remained.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so by that time, we had no illusions.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had no hope.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we prepared better.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Most families provided for some hiding places, decided to run into the forests, and so about 125 survived.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
